<DocsLayout title="Cube Effect">
  <h1>Cube Effect</h1>
  <p class="lead">Simulates a rotating 3D cube transition. The plugin enables <code>preserve-3d</code> and a <code>perspective</code> on the wrapper. Pair it with a CSS transition on the slides to animate the rotation.</p>

  <h2>Import</h2>
  <pre><code>import {"{"} cubeEffect {"}"} from '@andresclua/sliderkit-effects'</code></pre>

  <h2>Options</h2>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Option</th><th>Type</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>shadow</code></td><td><code>boolean</code></td><td>—</td><td>Reserved for a future shadow layer beneath the cube.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>slideShadows</code></td><td><code>boolean</code></td><td>—</td><td>Reserved for per-face shadow overlays.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>How it works</h2>
  <p>On install the plugin adds the class <code>c--slider-effect-cube</code> to the container and sets <code>transform-style: preserve-3d</code> and <code>perspective: 1200px</code> on the wrapper. Use CSS to position slides as cube faces and add transition animations.</p>

  <h2>Example</h2>
  <pre><code>{`import { createSlider } from '@andresclua/sliderkit'
import { cubeEffect } from '@andresclua/sliderkit-effects'
import { arrows } from '@andresclua/sliderkit-plugins'

createSlider('#my-slider', {
  loop: true,
  plugins: [
    cubeEffect(),
    arrows(),
  ],
})
`}</code></pre>

  <pre><code>{`/* CSS — animate slide transforms */
.c--slider-effect-cube .c--slider-a__item {
  transition: transform 500ms ease;
}
`}</code></pre>

  <p>For a full cube rotation preset using translate + rotateY, see the <a href="/docs/effects/creative">Creative Effect</a> page.</p>

  <p><a href="/demos/effect-cube">View cube effect demo</a></p>
</DocsLayout>
